A. Mission Description and Budget Item Justification
This project designs and develops mechanisms for the implementation of trusted artificial intelligence and machine learning (AI/ML) for processing, detecting, identifying,
and reacting to potentially adverse effects on AI/ML capabilities. It provides recommendations for countering adversarial AI/ML, improving algorithms, and ensuring
resilience in complex and contested environments. Effective use of Counter-AI to secure response mechanisms for the identification and detection of adversarial AI/ML
is critical to address threats in a rapidly evolving environment. These technologies will produce an AI solution that rapidly adjusts AI/ML algorithms to disregard and stop
malicious attempts to corrupt Army AI/ML tools.

 Work in this project is performed by the Artificial Intelligence Integration Center (AI2C).

