Will conduct research to develop proof-of-concept training and development methods for leadership, teams, and multiteam
systems; identify methods for increasing training throughput and effectiveness; initiate development of assessments and
interventions to enhance command and control (C2) decision advantage in the future operating environment; develop diagnostic
team assessments; compose Soldier attribute composition frameworks; identify critical knowledge, skills, abilities, and other
characteristics for the current and future operating environment; develop artificial intelligence (AI) tools to support talent
management initiatives.
FY 2026 to FY 2027 Increase/Decrease Statement:
FY 2027 funding decrease due to development and validation of fewer training methods for leadership and developmental
interventions for enhanced command and control.
